Alienware X17 R1. 
Although in some areas imperfect, the user experience for my first Alienware laptop has been indeed an elite gaming one. Thus, I have decided to go for another beast that was built by alien civilizations... Thus, here we are, again, in the "Alienware elite" boat. No regrets. There have been some bugs and unpleasant surprises, however, the Dell Support team has been stellar and my experience has been and still is an amazing one. I am currently using this laptop exclusively for gaming, and it delivers top quality framerate and world class performance in all applications. The cooling system is especially revolutionary and offering aggressive cooling performance, the shape of the fans and the use of a proprietary Alienware liquid metal / paste named Element 31 have, thus far, offered great gaming experiences. However, it has been a top quality user experience, but not a perfect one. In any case, all bugs, issues and unpleasant surprises have been, as usual, ideally handled by the stellar Dell Support team. 
Understandably so, the Alienware line of products is pushing the boundaries for performance, however, there can be moments where stability can be improved, both in terms of software, as well as OS communication, drivers and such. I feel that Dell have historically done their best to consider my feedback and that has shown in the quality of updates, in terms of drivers, BIOS, firmware and proprietary software handling power schemes, communication between devices and more.  
